<!-- ═══════════ MATHEMATICAL MODEL ═══════════ -->
<section id="model">
  <div class="section-label">Formal Model</div>
  <h2>Mathematical Foundations</h2>
  <p class="lead">
    ETDM is formalized as a complete mathematical system 
    $\mathfrak{F} = (G, \pi, \mathcal{S}, \mathcal{M}, \mathcal{C}, L, \Theta, f_{\text{discovery}}, f_{\text{app}})$ 
    with rigorous definitions for every component.
  </p>

  <div class="math-box">
    <h4>Network &amp; Loss Oracle</h4>
    <p>Communication graph $G = (V, E)$ with $n$ nodes. Deterministic loss oracle:</p>
    <p style="text-align:center; margin-top:1rem;">
      $$L(r, u, v, c) = \begin{cases} 1 \text{ (dropped)}, & \text{if } H(\text{seed}, r, u, v, c) < q_{u,v} \\ 0 \text{ (delivered)}, & \text{otherwise} \end{cases}$$
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem; color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.9rem;">
      where $H$ is a BLAKE2b hash and $q_{u,v} = \text{clamp}(q_{\text{base}} + \xi_{u,v},\; 0.01,\; 0.99)$.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="math-box">
    <h4>Hidden Twin Mapping</h4>
    <p>An involutive ground-truth mapping — unknown to the algorithm:</p>
    <p style="text-align:center; margin-top:1rem;">
      $$\pi: V \to V, \quad \pi(\pi(u)) = u, \quad \pi(u) \neq u \;\; \forall u \in V$$
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem; color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.9rem;">
      Twin links $(u, \pi(u))$ have loss rate $q_{\text{twin}} \ll q_{\text{base}}$, creating a discoverable signal.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="math-box">
    <h4>EWMA Scoring &amp; Twin Discovery</h4>
    <p>Each node maintains exponentially weighted scores for peers:</p>
    <p style="text-align:center; margin-top:1rem;">
      $$s_u(v, r{+}1) = (1 - \lambda)\, s_u(v, r) + \lambda \cdot o$$
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.5rem; color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.9rem;">
      Sigmoid confidence: $c_u(v,r) = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-\alpha \cdot s_u(v,r)}}$. Candidate selected as 
      $p_u^* = \arg\max_{v \in K_u \setminus (N(u) \cup \{u\})} s_u(v,r)$ with hysteresis threshold $\eta$.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="math-box">
    <h4>Three-Way Handshake Protocol</h4>
    <p>Twin locking follows a strict handshake with nonce verification:</p>
    <p style="text-align:center; margin-top:1rem;">
      $$u \xrightarrow{\text{PROPOSE}(n_u, k_u)} v \xrightarrow{\text{ACCEPT}(n_u, n_v, k_u)} u \xrightarrow{\text{CONFIRM}(n_v, k_u)} v$$
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.5rem; color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.9rem;">
      Upon completion: $L_u = 1, \text{tw}_u = v, L_v = 1, \text{tw}_v = u$ — the twin shortcut is active.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="math-box">
    <h4>Dynamic Extended Neighborhood</h4>
    <p>Once locked, the application layer gains an extra communication target:</p>
    <p style="text-align:center; margin-top:1rem;">
      $$N'_u(r) = \begin{cases} N(u) \cup \{\text{tw}_u(r)\}, & \text{if locked and } \text{tw}_u \notin N(u) \\ N(u), & \text{otherwise}\end{cases}$$
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════ ARCHITECTURE ═══════════ -->
<section id="architecture">
  <div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
  <h2>Protocol Phases &amp; State Machine</h2>
  <p class="lead">
    Each synchronous round consists of 5 ordered passes. The ETDM sub-layer operates 
    in passes 1-4, while the application algorithm executes in pass 5.
  </p>

  <div class="arch-diagram">
    <h4 style="color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.85rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">ROUND STRUCTURE</h4>
    <div class="arch-flow">
      <div class="arch-step">Pass 1<br><small>Proactive<br>HELLO / PROPOSE</small></div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step">Pass 2<br><small>Reactive<br>ACCEPT / REJECT</small></div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step">Pass 3<br><small>Remaining<br>CONFIRM</small></div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step">Pass 4<br><small>Timeouts<br>Score Decay</small></div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step" style="border-color:rgba(188,140,255,0.4); color:var(--accent-purple);">Pass 5<br><small>Application<br>Algorithm</small></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="arch-diagram">
    <h4 style="color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.85rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">NODE STATE MACHINE</h4>
    <div class="arch-flow">
      <div class="arch-step">IDLE</div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step">SEARCHING</div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step">PROPOSING</div>
      <span class="arch-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="arch-step" style="border-color:rgba(63,185,80,0.4); color:var(--accent-green);">LOCKED ✓</div>
    </div>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); font-size:0.8rem; margin-top:1rem;">
      Rollback: PROPOSING → SEARCHING (on REJECT/timeout) &nbsp;|&nbsp; LOCKED → SEARCHING (on heartbeat timeout)
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

