<!-- ═══════════ KEY INSIGHT ═══════════ -->
<section>
  <div class="section-label">Key Insight</div>
  <h2>When Does ETDM Help?</h2>
  <div class="math-box" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);">
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem; line-height:1.8;">
      <strong>ETDM excels</strong> when the algorithm's bottleneck is <em>global information propagation</em> 
      across a high-diameter network. The twin shortcut effectively halves the information propagation 
      distance, yielding the most dramatic improvements on Ring topologies and for problems like 
      Consensus (up to <strong>67.4% faster</strong>) and Leader Election.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem; line-height:1.8; margin-top:1rem;">
      <strong>ETDM is neutral</strong> when the problem is <em>inherently local</em> (MIS, Coloring) — 
      global shortcuts simply aren't utilized by the algorithm. This problem-dependent behavior 
      makes ETDM a <strong>targeted optimization tool</strong> rather than a universal replacement.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

